Subject: [PATCH] stratum: skip parent-style getblocktemplate job for pure-aux children

Yiimp's coind_create_job() unconditionally calls getblocktemplate on every
configured coind. For a pure-aux child served by a bitcoind-compat adapter
that only implements createauxblock/submitauxblock (ZCU), the RPC method
does not exist (-32601) and the call fails on every job cycle. That failure
prevents ZCU from ever entering the aux merge-mine rotation, so its hash
is never merkled into the scrypt work and no aux blocks are ever submitted.

TXC/ISK's adapters happen to expose getblocktemplate as a stub (it returns
error -8 "call with rules") so the RPC exists and the codepath survives,
which is why they work today. ZCU's adapter returns -32601 and dies.

The correct gate is auxpow_rpc_mode: when a coind is flagged aux AND uses
the custom-auxpow (createauxblock) path, stratum has no business asking it
for a parent-chain block template. Skip coind_create_job() for those coins.

Apply on the live tree, then rebuild + reinstall:

    cd /home/ubuntu/aws/LIVE/LIVE-FINAL/stratum
    sudo patch -p1 < /path/to/stratum-skip-aux-child-job.patch
    sudo make -j$(nproc)
    sudo install -m755 stratum /var/stratum/stratum
    sudo systemctl restart stratum-aws-scrypt

---
 stratum/coind_template.cpp | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

--- a/stratum/coind_template.cpp
+++ b/stratum/coind_template.cpp
@@ -564,6 +564,11 @@
 // coind_create_job — parent-chain job creation via getblocktemplate.
 bool coind_create_job(YAAMP_COIND *coind, bool force)
 {
+	// Pure-aux children (custom auxpow via createauxblock) have no
+	// getblocktemplate on their adapter — skip parent-style job creation.
+	// Their aux hash is fetched by coind_getauxblock_custom() elsewhere.
+	if (coind->isaux && coind_uses_custom_auxpow(coind)) return false;
+
 	bool b = rpc_connected(&coind->rpc);
 	if(!b) return false;
 
